comment_data.body:
It looks to me like pyx files don't have the implicit `cimport cython` added when they're tested and so `total_ordering` isn't being recognised

I think the easiest fix would be to add a `cimport cython`/`import cython` to both files (on line 1, just so they line up).

Tho `(c)import cython` [should be automatically included](https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4226#issuecomment-860553277).
And all of the previous related PRs didn't include it either. It's kind of a convention.

> Tho `(c)import cython` [should be automatically included](https://github.com/cython/cython/pull/4226#issuecomment-860553277). And all of the previous related PRs didn't include it either. It's kind of a convention.

Yes, but on the other hand it fixed failing build - not sure why

https://github.com/cython/cython/blob/579fcbc29bbc097af323a504447bebf6e2696231/runtests.py#L856

I think it's only applied to .py files

> I think it's only applied to .py files

Relaxing this condition to other than .py files is breaking the suite. Can we go with the PR as it is?
